Deputy Health Minister Sibongiseni Dhlomo says Charlotte Maxeke Hospital will be fully functional by the end of 2023. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Deputy Health Minister Sibongiseni Dhlomo says Charlotte Maxeke Hospital will be fully functional by the end of 2023. He says government is working on ramping up security at the hospital as vandalism has become a major issue. READ: Charlotte Maxeke Hospital | Time for excuses is over - Jack Bloom The accident and emergency units have been reopened after a fire destroyed the hospital over a year ago. It cost nearly R70-million for the repairs. Watch the video above for more details.